<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span><span class=3D"emoji-common-main-styles emoji-common-node   emoji-=
common-emoji-image   css-19bdfyn" title=3D":white_check_mark:">:tick:</span=
></span></p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The organisation the caller is operating in.<=
/p><p>Available values : WPAC, SGB, BSA, BOM, BTPL, UBS, VIRG, RAMS, BAS, W=
NZL</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><span style=3D"color=
: rgb(59,65,81);">x-originatingSystemId</span></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><span><span class=3D"emoji-common-main-styles emoji-common-node   emoji-=
common-emoji-image   css-19bdfyn" title=3D":white_check_mark:">:tick:</span=
></span></p>
</div></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Alfabet Id of calling application e.g. A00304=
. Must be propagated to APIs being invoked. Exception for partners calling =
in via partner APIs, do not populate this header as the partner=E2=80=99s c=
onsuming application name (eg. ptr-corelogic-valex) will be injected into t=
his field by the gateway.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
